x4freetext: SAME AS CEA-N-1338 EXCEPT GAMMA(GAMMA) AND GAMMA(TOT).
-MEASUREMENT AND ANALYSIS OF THE HOLMIUM TOTAL CROSS-
SECTION FOR NEUTRON ENERGIES BETWEEN 0.005 AND 1.7
PHOTO-NEUTRONS FROM A NATURAL URANIUM TARGET
THE SAMPLE WAS COOLED TO LIQUID NITROGEN
TEMPERATURE, 77.4 DEGREE K, T(EFF) = 107 DEGREE K.
FLIGHT PATH = 103.7 M FOR NEUTRON ENERGY 0.17 TO 3 KEV
FLIGHT PATH =  53.4 M FOR NEUTRON ENERGY 5 TO 390 EV.
.ONLY S-WAVE RESONANCES SEEN DUE TO THIN SAMPLE.
.DERIVED FROM THE LOW ENERGY REGION WHERE THE RESONANCE
CONTRIBUTION IS SMALL. THE VALUE REPRODUCES THE
POTENTIAL SCATTERING IN THE WHOLE ANALYSED REGION.
